p2
VThrilling violin trio
p3
sVnews
p4
VKomanduri Seshadri of Hyderabad and his talented sons Ananta Sowrirajan and Vikata Krishna gave a violin concert forSwarajhariSabha at Sri Sivaramakrishna Kshetram. A &#8216;Grade A&#8217; vocalist and violinist of All India Radio, Seshadri has a repertoire of thousands of compositions in Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam and Kannada. He holds a postgraduate degree in music and has worked in several government music colleges as lecturer and principal.The concert began with the Bhairavi varnamViribonifollowed by the Arabhi pancharatna keertanaSadhinchene.Janakiramanin Sudhaseemantini carried enjoyable kalpana swaras by the three.Deva Deva Kalayamiof Swathi Thirunal in Mayamalavagowla was also beautifully played by the trio with fine kalpana swara. After playingMakelarain Ravichandrika, they playedChakkani Rajamargamuin Karaharapriya for the main piece of the concert. The raga delineation, niraval and swaras were of high order and the keerta was played with rich bhava sense.Seshadri and his sons were supported by M. Lakshminarayana Raju on the mridangam and M. Haribabu on the ghatam. The concert came to a close with a tarangam and a ragamalika.
